Josefin Slab Thin Regular (JosefinSlab-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Josefin Slab' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Josefin Slab Thin'.

Josefin Slab Thin Italic (JosefinSlab-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'JosefinSlab-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Josefin Slab Thin Italic (JosefinSlab-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Josefin Slab' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Josefin Slab Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

NID 16 'Josefin Slab' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Josefin Slab Light'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'JosefinSlab-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Josefin Slab Light Italic (JosefinSlab-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Josefin Slab' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Josefin Slab Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Josefin Slab Italic (JosefinSlab-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'JosefinSlab-Italic', Everything looks good.

Josefin Slab SemiBold Italic (JosefinSlab-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Josefin Slab' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Josefin Slab SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Josefin Slab SemiBold Italic (JosefinSlab-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'JosefinSlab-Bold', Everything looks good.
